ZH: 1. 冬天来临时，许多动物会选择蛰伏起来。
EN: 1. Many animals choose to hibernate when winter arrives.
ZH: 2. 过去的几年里，他一直蛰伏在家中学习。
EN: 2. He has been hiding at home studying for the past few years.
ZH: 3. 大熊猫在寿命的大部分时间里都是蛰伏的。
EN: 3. Giant pandas hibernate for a large part of their lifespan.
ZH: 4. 这只母蛇正在寻找蛰伏的地方为它的蛋孵化。
EN: 4. The mother snake is looking for a place to hibernate and hatch her eggs.
ZH: 5. 应对困境时，他选择了蛰伏，等待时机。
EN: 5. When faced with difficulties, he chose to go into hiding and wait for the right moment.
ZH: 6. 在过去的十年里，这个小镇一直蛰伏在经济萧条的影响下。
EN: 6. The small town has been dormant under the impact of the economic downturn for the past decade.
ZH: 7. 消息传来，那位富有的商人决定蛰伏一段时间以避免媒体关注。
EN: 7. The news came that the wealthy businessman decided to go in hiding for a while to avoid media attention.
ZH: 8. 在这个城市的夏季，很少有人出门，它们更倾向于蛰伏在家中。
EN: 8. During the summer in this city, few people go out; they prefer to stay hidden at home.
ZH: 9. 这个地区的小村庄已经很久没有受到外界的关注，它就像蛰伏在山腹中一样。
EN: 9. The small village in this region has not received much attention for a long time; it is like hibernating in the mountainside.
ZH: 10. 这个时候，我们需要保持沉默，以便蛰伏在无形中。
EN: 10. Now is the time when we need to remain silent and go into hiding invisibly.
ZH: 11. 在寒冷的冬天，熊类会筑巢蛰伏。
EN: 11. In the cold winter, bears will build nests and hibernate.
ZH: 12. 鲟鱼是一种喜欢在水底蛰伏的远洋鱼类。
EN: 12. Sturgeons are a type of deep-sea fish that like to hibernate at the bottom of the water.
ZH: 13. 她感到疲惫不堪，需要一段时间蛰伏休息。
EN: 13. She felt exhausted and needed some time to rest and recuperate.
ZH: 14. 当风暴来临时，各种生物都选择蛰伏以保护自己。
EN: 14. When a storm comes, various organisms choose to go into hiding to protect themselves.
ZH: 15. 这个古老的传统已经蛰伏了几百年，直到最近才重新兴起。
EN: 15. This ancient tradition has been dormant for hundreds of years until recently when it resurfaced.
ZH: 16. 这只母狗刚生完小狗，现在正蛰伏在巢穴中照顾它们。
EN: 16. The mother dog just gave birth to puppies and is now hibernating in the den taking care of them.
ZH: 17. 在繁忙的夏季旅游季节结束后，这个岛屿会蛰伏几个月的时间。
EN: 17. After the busy summer tourist season, this island will hibernate for a few months.
ZH: 18. 这些蛇会在寒冷的冬天选择蛰伏，以保护自己并节省能量。
EN: 18. These snakes choose to hibernate during the cold winter to protect themselves and conserve energy.
ZH: 19. 这个城市在季节交替时会蛰伏一段时间，然后再次热闹起来。
EN: 19. This city will go into hiding for a while during seasonal transitions and then become lively again.
ZH: 20. 蛰伏是一种良好的适应策略，可以在恶劣环境中生存。
EN: 20. Hibernation is a good survival strategy that allows adaptation in harsh environments.
